theorem Topology.interior_closure_univ_iff_closure_univ {X : Type*}
    [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (closure A) = (Set.univ : Set X) ↔ closure A = Set.univ := by
  constructor
  · intro h
    apply Set.Subset.antisymm
    · intro x _
      have hx : x ∈ interior (closure A) := by
        have : x ∈ (Set.univ : Set X) := by
          simp
        simpa [h] using this
      exact interior_subset hx
    · intro _ _; trivial
  · intro h_dense
    exact
      Topology.interior_closure_eq_univ_of_dense (X := X) (A := A) h_dense

import Mathlib
import Aesop

theorem Topology.P3_of_dense' {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    closure A = (Set.univ : Set X) → Topology.P3 A := by
  intro h_dense
  dsimp [Topology.P3]
  intro x _hxA
  -- Since `closure A = univ`, its interior is also `univ`, so every point lies inside it.
  have : x ∈ interior (closure A) := by
    have : x ∈ (Set.univ : Set X) := by
      simp
    simpa [h_dense, interior_univ] using this
  exact this

theorem Topology.interior_closure_closure_eq {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    interior (closure (closure A)) = interior (closure A) := by
  simpa [closure_closure]
